        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: MADD is highly detected in soluble synaptic subcellular fractions by immunoblot analysis (Fig 1). IF localisation data in Fig 2 suggests a partial synaptic localisation. However only single antibody stainings were performed.. Experimental description: Material and Methods \"Subcellular fractionation of rat brain was carried out as described.\"" ;
